text: "Princess of Egypt" is a 1999 song recorded by Swedish musician known under the pseudonym of E-Type and is produced by David Kreuger and Per Magnusson. It is the third single from his third album, Last Man Standing, and was a tribute to his longtime backing vocalist, Nana Hedin. The chorus vocals are by Swedish singer Jeanette Soderholm. The song peaked at number 9 on the Swedish singles chart with 11 weeks on the chart.
